trend_summary: Imagery reveals steady suburban infill: scattered vacant lots replaced by houses and commercial sheds, modest road extensions, expansion of a civic complex south. Parkland along the river remains but sports facilities are upgraded. Tree canopy and riparian vegetation thicken, offsetting slight build-up growth. Overall built form stays medium-density suburban with balanced green-to-roof ratio.
notable_changes: Southern corner gains a large white-roof civic/school building and adjacent parking.
New commercial/warehouse roofs appear along the central west arterial corridor.
Vacant residential lots infilled, tightening street grid in the north-central blocks.
Baseball complex upgraded: extra diamonds, improved turf and access roads.
Riverbank shows thicker riparian tree cover and expansion of vegetated buffer.
